ctivity Reports**:\n   - Generate productivity reports for analysis.\n   - Include metrics such as task completion rates, time spent on tasks, etc.\n\n6. **Adaptive Scheduling**:\n   - Dynamically adjust task assignments based on team member availability.\n   - Adjust schedules based on project priorities.\n\n### Example Implementation Steps\n\n1. **Task Input and Management**:\n   - Implement methods to add, update, and delete tasks.\n   - Implement methods to set and update task priorities.\n   - Implement methods to allocate time slots for tasks.\n\n2. **Real-Time Tracking**:\n   - Implement a method to update task statuses.\n   - Implement a method to track progress in real-time.\n\n3. **Communication Features**:\n   - Implement a simple messaging system or chat feature.\n\n4. **Reminders and Notifications**:\n   - Implement a method to send reminders for upcoming tasks.\n   - Implement a method to send notifications for task updates and deadlines.\n\n5. **Productivity Reports**:\n   - Implement a method to generate productivity reports.\n   - Include metrics such as task completion rates, time spent on tasks, etc.\n\n6. **Adaptive Scheduling**:\n   - Implement a method to dynamically adjust task assignments based on team member availability.\n   - Implement a method to adjust schedules based on project priorities.\n\n### Next Task\n\n**Task 3**: Implement the missing functionalities in `solution.py`.\n\nHere is an example of how you might start implementing some of these functionalities:\n\n```python\n# solution.py\n\nclass TeamSyncPro:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.tasks = {}  # Dictionary to store tasks with their details\n        self.messages = []  # List to store messages for communication\n\n    def add_task(self, task_id, description, priority, time_slot):\n        """Add a new task."""\n        self.tasks[task_id] = {\n            \'description\': description,\n            \'priority\': priority,\n            \'time_slot\': time_slot,\n        